rades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20about%20the%20tanks%2C%20Pentagon%20spokesperson%20Lt.%20Col.%20Charlie%20Dietz%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20Department%20of%20Defense%20%26quot%3Bcan't%20provide%20the%20specifics%20on%20the%20details%20but%20can%20confirm%20that%20they%20were%20the%20export%20variants.%26quot%3B%20That%20confirmation%20indicates%20that%20the%20armor%20on%20the%20Abrams%20tanks%2C%20among%20certain%20other%20things%2C%20was%20downgraded%20prior%20to%20delivery.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2255ab62ef-aee5-45ee-a095-823dc54a0b99%5C%22%3EA%20different%20type%20of%20war%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20war%20is%20a%20particularly%20intense%20conflict%20and%20different%20from%20ones%20the%20West%20has%20fought%2C%20with%20drones%20being%20used%20more%20than%20in%20any%20other%20conflict%20in%20history%20and%20a%20huge%20amount%20of%20missiles%20and%20artillery%20in%20play.%20Combat%20vehicles%20of%20all%20types%20have%20struggled.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20Ukrainian%20soldiers%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fformer-us-general-rejects-criticism-from-ukrainians-of-abrams-tanks-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%20the%20armor%20the%20Abrams%20tanks%20came%20with%20%26quot%3Bis%20not%20sufficient%20for%20this%20moment%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20so%20many%20drones%20attacking%20from%20above.%20Drones%20have%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvideo-drone-destroyed-exposed-tank-russia-adapting-growing-threat-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20been%20used%20to%20damage%20and%20destroy%20tanks%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20well%20as%20to%20guide%20other%20weaponry%20to%20hit%20the%20vehicles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Screengrab%20from%20a%20video%20of%20a%20Ukrainian%20drone%20targeting%20a%20Russian%20tank%20in%20the%20Bakhmut%20sector%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66618b4ccc442a2f676e6ea0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221406%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EScreengrab%20from%20a%20video%20of%20a%20Ukrainian%20drone%20targeting%20a%20Russian%20tank%20in%20the%20Bakhmut%20sector%20in%20May%202024.%3Cp%3EX%2F%40DefenceU%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDe%20Bretton-Gordon%20said%20a%20lot%20of%20Ukraine's%20additions%20%26quot%3Bare%20very%20much%20focused%20on%20the%20drones%20because%20the%20mass%20use%20of%20drones%20is%20something%20that%20is%20new%20to%20this%20conflict.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInnovations%20like%20cage%20armor%20are%20seen%20as%20necessary%20considering%20that%20on%20many%20Western%20and%20Russian%20tanks%2C%20even%20with%20newer%20armor%20upgrades%2C%20the%20protection%20on%20the%20top%20is%20much%20thinner%20than%20elsewhere%20on%20the%20body%20of%20the%20tank%2C%20which%20Ukraine%20often%20strengthens%20with%20reactive%20armor%20additions%20to%20provide%20an%20extra%20defensive%20layer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNobody%20really%20expected%20attack%20from%20above%2C%20which%20is%20why%20they're%20so%20vulnerable%2C%26quot%3B%20De%20Bretton-Gordon%20said.%20The%20Abrams%20was%20notably%20designed%20and%20built%20to%20fight%20Soviet%20tanks%2C%20not%20dodge%20airborne%20threats%2C%20and%20the%20tank%20gained%20a%20lot%20of%20its%20reputation%20in%20battles%20with%20air%20cover.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20where%20tanks%20are%20vulnerable%20has%20now%20changed%2C%20with%20drones%20able%20to%20attack%20directly%20or%20drop%20devices%20like%20hand%20grenades%20onto%20them%20%E2%80%94%20something%20that%20has%20caused%20Russian%20tanks%20to%20explode%2C%20often%20by%20causing%20the%20ammunition%20inside%20to%20cook%20off.%20Western%20tanks%20like%20the%20American%20Abrams%20have%20a%20better%20design%20to%20prevent%20that%2C%20but%20the%20vehicles%20still%20have%20vulnerabilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETanks%20in%20this%20war%20also%20face%20the%20threat%20of%20artillery%20and%20anti-tank%20guided%20missiles%2C%20making%20the%20battlespace%20more%20dangerous%20for%20tanks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDrummond%20said%20%26quot%3Bthe%20Russians%20are%20equipped%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20anti-tank%20weapons%20and%20in%20the%20assault%20on%20an%20enemy%20position%2C%20you're%20going%20to%20get%20overwhelmed%20with%20anti-tank%20assault%2C%20so%20you%20do%20need%20armor.%26quot%3B%20Ukraine%20needs%20as%20much%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222e0c2a36-4fb9-4271-a254-085416375e03%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ENot%20enough%20Western%20tanks%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20described%20Russia%20and%20Ukraine%20as%20being%20in%20a%20kind%20of%20race%2C%20as%20is%20typical%20in%20war.%20%26quot%3BAs%20soon%20as%20somebody%20comes%20up%20with%20an%20advantage%2C%20somebody%20else%20will%20come%20back%20with%20a%20countermeasure%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20Russia%20and%20Ukraine%20have%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-war-shows-tanks-need-cages-protect-from-exploding-drones-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emodifying%20some%20of%20their%20tanks%20and%20other%20armored%20vehicles%20by%20putting%20cages%20on%20top%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Russia's%20innovations%20have%20included%20a%20strange-looking%20structure%20that%20led%20to%20its%20tanks%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-turtle-tanks-maybe-not-as-crazy-as-they-seem-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebeing%20called%20%26quot%3Bturtle%20tanks.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221920%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20%26quot%3Bturtle%20tank%26quot%3B%20rolls%20onto%20the%20battlefield%20at%20the%20head%20of%20a%20convoy%2C%20a%20T-72%20is%20driven%20by%20Russian%20forces%20next%20to%20the%20Kremlin.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F661f66df49058e669356ca2a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Russian%20%26quot%3Bturtle%20tank%26quot%3B%20seen%20in%20Ukrainian%20drone%20footage.%3Cp%3EScreenshot%2FTelegram%20via%20%40Khortytsky_wind%2C%20ALEXANDER%20NEMENOV%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20war%20has%20been%20a%20tough%20one%20for%20tanks.%20Russia%20had%20lost%20more%20than%203%2C000%20as%20of%20February%2C%20the%20International%20Institute%20for%20Strategic%20Studies%20reported%20at%20the%20time.%20And%20Ukraine%20has%20lost%20tanks%20too%2C%20including%20at%20least%20five%20of%20its%2031%20Abrams.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine%20having%20so%20few%20of%20them%2C%20many%20experts%20say%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-abrams-tanks-keep-drones-away-need-more-protection-commander-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehas%20made%20things%20difficult%20for%20Ukraine%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20it%20has%20to%20keep%20the%20precious%20few%20it%20has%20intact%2C%20and%20it%20doesn't%20have%20enough%20to%20mount%20any%20large%20armor%20offensives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDe%20Bretton-Gordon%20said%20that%20if%20Ukraine%20had%20more%20Abrams%20and%20Challenger%20tanks%2C%20%26quot%3Bthey%20would%20use%20them%20differently.%26quot%3B%20But%20instead%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20drip%20feeding%20of%20kit'%26quot%3B%20to%20Ukraine%20means%20%26quot%3Bthey've%20been%20fighting%20with%20one%20hand%20behind%20their%20back.%26quot%3B%20Ukrainian%20President%20Volodymyr%20Zelenksyy%20has%20lamented%20the%20limited%20number%20of%20Abrams.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbradley-fighting-vehicles-prove-worth-ukraine-short-on-abrams-tanks-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBradleys%20have%20been%20seen%20as%20more%20successful%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20even%20taking%20on%20Russian%20tanks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20least%20part%20of%20the%20explanation%20may%20be%20that%20Ukraine%20has%20been%20given%20more%2C%20at%20more%20than%20300.%20De%20Bretton-Gordon%20said%20it%20was%20key%20that%20Ukraine%20%26quot%3Bhas%20a