be%20worth%20it%20for%20some%20problems.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EChat%20GPT-5%2C%20the%20next%20version%20of%20OpenAI's%20language%20model%20that%20changed%20everything%2C%20is%20on%20the%20way.%20Business%20Insider%20previously%20reported%20that%20some%20customers%20have%20received%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-launch-better-gpt-5-chatbot-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edemos%20of%20the%20new%20version%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20speculation%20about%20improvements%20is%20rife.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-gpt5-what-is-at-stake-sam-altman-ai-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estakes%20are%20high%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20this%20model%20as%20it%20will%20solidify%20OpenAI's%20place%20at%20the%20forefront%20of%20AI%20or%20shove%20it%20to%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20pack.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20AI%20developers%20wait%20to%20test%20GPT-5%2C%20some%20have%20found%20a%20new%20way%20to%20bootstrap%20their%20way%20to%20more%20advanced%20AI%20without%20an%20entirely%20new%20model.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJared%20Quincy%20Davis%20is%20the%20CEO%20of%20Foundry%2C%20an%20AI%20cloud%20service%20provider%20employing%20new%20strategies%20to%20make%20graphics%20processing%20unit%20computing%20more%20efficient.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20startup%20emerged%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffinance.yahoo.com%2Fnews%2Fexclusive-foundry-comes-stealth-350-115151375.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estealth%20in%20March%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20%2480%20million%20in%20seed%20funding%20co-led%20by%20Lightspeed%20Venture%20Partners%20and%20Sequoia%20Capital%2C%20for%20which%20Davis%20was%20formerly%20a%20startup%20scout%20specializing%20in%20AI%2C%20and%20a%20%24350%20million%20valuation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFoundry's%20strategies%20center%20on%20cycling%20AI%20workloads%20across%20GPUs%20to%20maximize%20GPU%20utilization.%20Fewer%20idle%20GPUs%20then%20translate%20to%20more%20affordable%20computing%2C%20as%20Davis%20explained%20on%20the%20No%20Priors%20podcast%20released%20Thursday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDavis'%20method%20of%20boosting%20the%20performance%20of%20existing%20large%20language%20models%2C%20which%20fits%20within%20an%20emerging%20classification%20of%20%26quot%3BCompound%20AI%20Systems%2C%26quot%3B%20was%20explained%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscholar.google.com%2Fcitations%3Fview_op%3Dview_citation%26hl%3Den%26user%3D_3bb%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresearch%20paper%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20last%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20gist%20is%20that%20if%20you%20ask%20a%20model%20like%20Chat%20GPT-4%20the%20same%20question%20repeatedly%2C%20you%20can%20use%20another%2C%20much%20smaller%20model%20to%20analyze%20those%20responses%20and%20pick%20the%20best%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMore%20and%20more%20often%2C%20to%20go%20beyond%20the%20capabilities%20and%20frontier%20accessible%20to%20today's%20state%20of%20the%20art%20models%20and%20kind%20of%20get%20GPT-5%20or%20GPT-6%20early%2C%20practitioners%20are%20starting%20to%20do%20these%20things%2C%20oftentimes%20implicitly%2C%20where%20they'll%20call%20the%20current%20state-of-the-art%20model%20many%2C%20many%20times%2C%26quot%3B%20Davis%20told%20podcast%20hosts%20Sarah%20Guo%20and%20Elad%20Gil.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDavis%20explained%20that%20his%20repeated%20%26quot%3Bcalling%26quot%3B%20of%20models%20is%20what%20some%20of%20the%20smartest%2C%20yet%20smallest%20models%20on%20the%20market%20have%20done%20in%20their%20training%20process.%20But%20right%20now%2C%20this%20method%20is%20only%20effective%20for%20certain%20kinds%20of%20queries%20%E2%80%94%20essentially%20questions%20with%20an%20answer%20that%20is%20easier%20to%20check%20than%20generate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20the%20kind%20of%20subjects%20you%20would%20expect%2C%20math%2C%20physics%2C%20electrical%20engineering%2C%20this%20type%20of%20approach%20was%20really%20helpful%2C%26quot%3B%20Davis%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20test%2C%20Davis%20gave%20GPT-4%20a%20challenging%20math%20problem.%20The%20model%20only%20got%20the%20correct%20answer%204%25%20of%20the%20time%2C%20but%20could%20tell%20which%20answers%20were%20correct%20when%20presented%20with%20options%2090%25%20of%20the%20time.%20When%20Davis%20and%20his%20co-authors%20used%20the%20compound%20AI%20method%2C%20the%20layered%20model%20produced%20the%20correct%20answer%2037%25%20of%20the%20time%20%E2%80%94%20a%20nearly%2010-fold%20increase.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBootstrapping%20improvements%20to%20foundation%20models%20isn't%20exactly%20more%20efficient%20%E2%80%94%20this%20method%20is%20almost%20certainly%20a%20more%20expensive%20way%20to%20leverage%20AI%20models%2C%20but%20in%20some%20cases%2C%20the%20improved%20results%20are%20well%20worth%20the%20cost%2C%20Davis%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20indicated%20that%20spending%20more%20on%20training%20and%20iterating%20now%20could%20save%20on%20inference%20computing%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20people%20are%20getting%20more%20sophisticated%20at%20thinking%20about%20cost%20in%20more%20of%20a%20life-cycle%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20Davis%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20you%20tested%20Chat%20GPT-5%3F%20Have%20a%20tip%20or%20an%20insight%20to%20share%3F%20Contact%20Emma%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aecosgrove%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Eecosgrove%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%20or%20use%20the%20secure%20messaging%20app%20Signal%3A%20443-333-9088%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffoundry-ceo-hack-improving-ai-models-gpt-5-2024-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1724403601000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6606b29216bde8d4ead37df8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%2