originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fnepal-at-least-14-people-killed-after-bus-veers-off-road-and-plunges-towards-river-13201445%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22At%20least%2014%20people%20have%20been%20killed%20after%20a%20bus%20carrying%20dozens%20of%20pilgrims%20from%20India%20came%20off%20a%20major%20road%20in%20central%20Nepal%2C%20officials%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fnepal-at-least-14-people-killed-after-bus-veers-off-road-and-plunges-towards-river-13201445%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22When%20Will%20Sunita%20Williams%20Come%20Back%20To%20Earth%3F%20Nasa%20Shares%20Big%20Update%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAstronauts%20Sunita%20Williams%20and%20Butchwilmore%20have%20been%20stuck%20in%20space%20since%20June%206%20and%20are%20hoping%20to%20make%20their%20way%20back%20to%20Earth%20soon%2C%20but%20Nasa%20says%20they%20may%20have%20to%20spend%20the%20next%20few%20days%20in%20uncertainty%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENASA%20is%20expected%20to%20take%20a%20final%20decision%20on%20Saturday%20to%20bring%20Sunita%20Williams%20back%20to%20Earth%20on%20Boeing's%20Starliner%20spacecraft%20or%20on%20SpaceX's%20Dragon%20capsule%2C%20the%20US%20space%20agency%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNASA's%20decision%20on%20whether%20to%20return%20Starliner%20to%20Earth%20with%20astronauts%20aboard%20is%20expected%20no%20earlier%20than%20August%2024%20(Saturday)%20at%20the%20conclusion%20of%20an%20agency-level%20review%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20space%20agency%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20began%20as%20an%20eight-day%20sojourn%20on%20the%20International%20Space%20Station%20(ISS)%20has%20extended%20to%20more%20than%20two%20months%20in%20space%20for%20Williams%20and%20Willmore%20--%20the%20duo%20who%20became%20the%20first%20to%20ride%20the%20much-delayed%20Starliner.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Starliner%20approached%20the%20orbiting%20lab%2C%20the%20spacecraft%20experienced%20a%20series%20of%20technical%20issues%20such%20as%20the%20failure%20of%20several%20thrusters%20and%20helium%20leaks%20in%20the%20propulsion%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20engineers%20were%20able%20to%20bring%20four%20of%20the%20five%20malfunctioning%20thrusters%20back%20online%20(there%20are%2028%20thrusters%20on%20Starliner)%2C%20it%20still%20raises%20a%20concern%20about%20%E2%80%9Ca%20successful%20de-orbit%E2%80%9D%20to%20Earth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20Boeing%20proclaimed%20the%20safety%20of%20Starliner%2C%20NASA%20officials%20have%20disagreed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20US%20space%20agency%20deems%20Starliner%20unfit%20to%20travel%20on%20Saturday%2C%20it%20would%20undock%20uncrewed%20from%20the%20orbiting%20lab.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWilliams%20and%20Wilmore%20will%20return%20onboard%20a%20SpaceX%20Dragon%20capsule%20in%20February%202025%2C%20as%20NASA%20has%20delayed%20the%20launch%20of%20the%20SpaceX%20Crew-9%20mission%20to%20the%20ISS%20to%20September%2024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20many%20setbacks%20for%20years%2C%20Boeing%20launched%20its%20first%20flight%20on%20June%205.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETogether%20with%20SpaceX%2C%20the%20company%20signed%20a%20contract%20in%202014%20with%20NASA's%20Commercial%20Crew%20Programme%20to%20fly%20operational%20missions%20to%20and%20from%20the%20space%20station.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202019%2C%20its%20debut%20uncrewed%20orbital%20flight%20mission%20did%20not%20go%20as%20planned.%20The%20mission%20was%20completed%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpaceX's%20Dragon%20capsules%20have%20been%20launching%20astronauts%20to%20space%20on%20its%20Falcon%209%20rockets%20since%202020.%20It%20has%20so%20far%20aced%20about%2012%20flights%20to%20the%20Space%20Station.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20Boeing%20has%20poured%20over%20%241.5%20billion%20into%20its%20Starliner%20programme%2C%20NASA%20has%20paid%20the%20aerospace%20giant%20about%20%244.2%20billion%20over%2